<TITLE> No duty for electronic goods in airport baggage </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam has proposed duty-free clearance for ordinary electronic appliances from airports by amending baggage rules. "Non-resident Bangladeshi foreign exchange earners bring with them some ordinary electronic appliances when they come back home," said Mirza Aziz. "But they face difficulties clearing those items at airports as these items are subject to duties and taxes."
